OL,3,CNovichok victim's mum says family took
OL,4,Ccomfort that nobody else died
OL,6,FThe deputy chief constable of
OL,7,FWiltshire Police said the force were
OL,8,Finitially treating Dawn's poisoning as
OL,9,Fa drugs overdose, then a drugs
OL,10,Foverdose with potential pesticide
OL,11,Fpoisoning, which was referred to as a
OL,12,F"bad batch incident".
OL,14,FPaul Mills told the inquiry samples
OL,15,Fhad been sent off "as a precaution",
OL,16,Fthen the next day he received an
OL,17,Fupdate and was told the testing had
OL,18,Fcome back "and it indicated Novichok".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/15
