OL,3,CNovichok victim's mum says family took
OL,4,Ccomfort that nobody else died
OL,6,F"Again, although we are devastated by
OL,7,Fher death, our family find comfort
OL,8,Fthat Dawn was the only life lost that
OL,9,Fday when the potential harm was much,
OL,10,Fmuch more.
OL,12,F"We know she would agree."
OL,14,FCommander Dominic Murphy, head of the
OL,15,FMet's Counter Terrorism Command,
OL,16,Fcalled the probe into the Novichok
OL,17,Fpoisonings an "unprecedented
OL,18,Finvestigation".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G13/15
