OL,3,CNovichok victim's mum says family took
OL,4,Ccomfort that nobody else died
OL,6,F"Having worked on the Litvinenko
OL,7,Finvestigation, I understood quite
OL,8,Fquickly how significant this would be
OL,9,Fand how completely challenging it
OL,10,Fwould be, so from even our senior
OL,11,Finvestigations through to how we would
OL,12,Fwork with partners to understand who
OL,13,Fmight be responsible for it, the scale
OL,14,Fof the incident, the impact on the
OL,15,Fpublic of Salisbury, this really was
OL,16,Fan unprecedented investigation, not
OL,17,Fone that we had seen before, but one
OL,18,Fthat we were able to apply our
OL,19,Fexisting operational processes to in
OL,20,Forder to respond."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G15/15
